sec.p:
Specimens were collected using an aspirator, some of them were extracted from litter using a Berlese-Tullgren funnel. The specimens were cleared in Nesbitt’s fluid, subsequently mounted on slides using Hoyer’s solution and dried for 6–10 days in oven at 50°C. Figures were drawn with Nikon phase contrast microscope (
80i
) and prepared for publication using Adobe Photoshop CS2.

